            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34610",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is related to ZF-6679\n\nBasically, the intention was that getOptions would preserve the original case, but lookups (getOption and hasOption) would work if you supply a lowercase key or a case sensitive key.\n\nBut, passing a key with a capital letter does not work.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-18T05:49:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-18T05:49:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34612",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Unit tests and fix to allow passing keys with capital letters to getOption and hasOption. getOption didn't need a fix since it was already coded to be case-insensitive, but relied on hasOption which was case-sensitive.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=travisp",
                        "name": "travisp",
                        "displayName": "Travis Pew",
